---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="description" content="Avijya Shrestha's personal website" />
    <meta name="author" content="Avijya Shrestha" />
    <meta
      name="keywords"
      content="avijya, shrestha, avijya shrestha, software developer, software engineer, developer, engineer, web developer, web engineer, web developer in sydney, web engineer in sydney"
    />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <title>avijya.sh</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <section id="intro">
        <h1>Avijya Shrestha</h1>
        <span class="devanagari">अविज्य श्रेष्ठ</span>
        <p>
          Software developer in Sydney. I build full-stack things, maintain AUR
          packages, and keep a home server alive.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="work">
        <h2>Selected Work</h2>

        <article>
          <h3><a href="https://sunsets-on-a-map.com">Sunsets</a></h3>
          <p class="stack">
            React · Hono · Postgres + PostGIS · TensorFlow.js · MapLibre GL JS
          </p>
          <p>
            Map and share sunset observations. Photos get classified on upload
            and pinned to an interactive map.
          </p>
          <div class="links">
            <a href="https://sunsets-on-a-map.com">Live</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/up-the-hill/sunsets-on-a-map">GitHub</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3>
            <a
              href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ffcdlpjolgglihiapammdhbdogcgjbki"
              >Blackout</a
            >
          </h3>
          <p class="stack">JavaScript · Browser Extension</p>
          <p>
            Create blackout poetry on any web page. Available on Chrome and
            Firefox.
          </p>
          <div class="links">
            <a
              href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ffcdlpjolgglihiapammdhbdogcgjbki"
              >Chrome</a
            >
            <a
              href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/blackout-poetry/"
              >Firefox</a
            >
            <a href="https://github.com/up-the-hill/blackout">GitHub</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3>
            <a href="https://daily-art-gallery.vercel.app">Daily Art Gallery</a>
          </h3>
          <p class="stack">TypeScript · Preact · Vite</p>
          <p>
            A new artwork from the Art Institute of Chicago every day. Seeded
            PRNG — no backend.
          </p>
          <div class="links">
            <a href="https://daily-art-gallery.vercel.app">Live</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/up-the-hill/daily-art-gallery">GitHub</a
            >
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="experience">
        <h2>Experience</h2>

        <article>
          <h3>Software Developer Intern @ Robotic Marketer</h3>
          <p class="meta">
            Jul 2025 – Nov 2025 · Sydney, NSW · Macquarie PACE Program
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Built a full-stack project management app (Django + React) on a
              4-person team; adopted as a client-facing product for 10,000+
              clients.
            </li>
            <li>
              Designed MongoDB schemas for project data, tasks, comments, and
              user assignments.
            </li>
            <li>
              Automated email notifications via SendGrid on mentions and project
              updates.
            </li>
            <li>
              Integrated OpenAI LLM for content generation and in-app chatbot.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="skills">
        <h2>Skills</h2>
        <dl>
          <dt>Languages</dt>
          <dd>
            C/C++, Java, JavaScript, TypeScript, HTML, CSS, Python, Bash, Go
          </dd>

          <dt>Frameworks</dt>
          <dd>React, Node.js, Next.js, Django, Hono, Express, Flutter</dd>

          <dt>Tools</dt>
          <dd>
            Git, AWS, Google Cloud, CI/CD, Terraform / OpenTofu, Docker,
            Ansible, Linux
          </dd>

          <dt>Databases</dt>
          <dd>PostgreSQL, Firebase, MongoDB, Redis</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section id="about">
        <h2>About</h2>
        <p>Arch Linux, Neovim, self-hosted everything. Blender on weekends.</p>
        <p><a href="/resume.pdf">Download résumé →</a></p>
